#1412: The Truth Detector




Original Air Date: 03.22.2014
 



Description:

 
This week on Car Talk, 

  Tom and Ray help test a device that should strike fear in the hearts
     of all mechanics: 
        a voice biometrics-based lie detector.

 Elsewhere, Corinne can't seem to get an oil change without 
     a broken dipstick as a bonus; 

 Christine's keys are stuck in her ignition--which may not be too worrisome,
   since her car won't start; 

 and can struggling musician Dan fix his van's exhaust with guitar strings
    and an orange juice can? 

  Also, a story that offers even more proof why you should never drive like Tommy!

       All this and more, this week on Car Talk.
